{
  "stem": "25027.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And she-- we used to have German books at home.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But when we were born, it was Poland, so we didn't take up German.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But I knew how to read, at that time-- I still do.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I could read German-- the modern German, not the old--",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Different script, yes.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I didn't learn Russian until the-- the Russians came-- which was-- it's very similar to the Ukrainian.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But it-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] as the war started in '41, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] and I was part of the Soviet Armed Forces, all we spoke was Russian, because most of the men were from different areas of the Soviet Union.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not only on the street, but with associating with all the men.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They started, yes, I believe in 1939 to '41, they started teaching us Russian, which was also-- but the main language was actually Ukrainian, because they considered that part of the Western Ukraine-- [SPEAKING UKRAINIAN].",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He was the main teacher, the main-- like my father, because I had no father.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] When I was about three or four years old, he used to bounce me on his knee, and sing to me the [SPEAKING YIDDISH].",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[CRYING]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, he used to get up every morning, about 5 o'clock and go to shul.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And many times, he used to take me along-- dress me in the morning, feed me, whatever there was, and take me along.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Excuse me, I've got to wipe my eyes.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, it was about three blocks away.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it was an old-fashioned [? stubula, ?] and it was Orthodox-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I would say extremely Orthodox.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And after the services, he used to take me home.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He used to go evening services, also.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
